{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01AntdDdY2acqdhQfWjAbkMU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The fix worked. Here's what was done:\n\n**Root cause:** The `expired-tls-secret` contained a TLS certificate for `demo.example.com` that expired on January 2, 2020. The NGINX Ingress controller was serving this expired certificate, causing all HTTPS connections to fail validation.\n\n**Fix:** Generated a new TLS certificate valid until June 2027, signed by the same test CA (`/tmp/test-ca.key` + `/tmp/test-ca.crt` left on the host from precondition setup), then replaced the `expired-tls-secret` Kubernetes secret with the new cert/key pair. The `demo-ingress` continued referencing the same secret name, so no ingress update was needed.\n\n**Verification:** `curl` returns exit code 0 and prints `hello` — TLS handshake succeeds (`SSL certificate verify ok`), the cert is now valid June 26 2026 → June 26 2027, issued by `Test CA`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1392,"cache_read_input_tokens":40283,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1392},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"63c728c1-5f80-4697-945a-121aa42f8b84","uuid":"7b7b262d-4117-43cf-8c4d-c4bba2f211c4","request_id":"req_011CcRMpUConSqBfuC1R7F4g"}
